# django_with_oauth — Client Service (`client_serv`)

A Django application acting as an **OAuth 2.0 client**, designed to run alongside an authorization server and a resource server in Docker Compose. It handles the Authorization Code flow (with optional PKCE), exchanges codes for tokens, and fetches protected resources.

---

## 🚀 Features

- **OAuth 2.0 Authorization Code flow**  
- Optional **PKCE** (Proof Key for Code Exchange) support  
- Secure token exchange and session storage  
- Fetches protected resources via authenticated HTTP calls  
- Robust error handling and detailed logging  
- Simple template rendering of received data  
- Fully containerized with Docker Compose  

---

## 📦 Prerequisites

- **Docker** (version 20.10+)  
- **Docker Compose** (version 1.29+)  

---

## 📁 Repository Layout

```text
django_with_oauth/
├── auth_server/            # OAuth2 provider & JWT generator
│   ├── Dockerfile
│   └── ...
├── resource_server/        # Protected resource API
│   ├── Dockerfile
│   └── ...
├── client_serv/            # This Django OAuth client
│   ├── Dockerfile
│   ├── client_app/
│   │   ├── views.py        # oauth_login, oauth_callback, client_login
│   │   └── …
│   ├── client_server/
│   │   ├── settings.py     # Loads env vars via python-decouple
│   │   ├── urls.py         # URL routes
│   │   └── …
│   ├── templates/
│   │   └── app.html        # Renders fetched resource data
│   ├── requirements.txt
│   ├── .env.example
│   └── README.md           # (this file)
├── docker-compose.yml
└── LICENSE
